Dear friends, sorry when I took a long time to text you back or can't go out to meet.

No, I don't hate you,
No, I'm not avoiding you.

I'm just struggling to heal & preserving energy. 

Being there is enough for me, but warm food & good hug work as well

Another thing about suicidal thoughts, whenever I have them, I can't seem to remember everyone who cared exist.

Truthfully, I deeply appreciate my friends who didn't give up on me & care to text about my health. 
Thank you for your patience,
thank you for being there.

Sometimes I would self isolate to preserve my energy.

In some cases, the best I can do for the day is to open my eyes and breathe, since all my energy is drained out. 
The worst would be suicidal thoughts.

It's a constant struggle.

People with depression disorder will require a lot of effort to focus on a task and our energy depleted much faster compared normal human.

Especially during depressive relapses, our energy is very limited while battling other physical symptoms.
